RDV - Realtime Data Viewer - NEESit Event Marker Branch
by Jason P. Hanley <jphanley@buffalo.edu>
modified by Lawrence J. Miler <ljmiller@sdsc.edu>



Release
-------
Version: 0.1
Date: 11/16/05


Introduction
------------

RDV is a software package used to view time synchronized,
streaming data, in live or archived form, over the internet from a
Data Turbine server. It is capable of displaying any time series data,
whether numeric, image, or video, in an integrated application for
viewing and analysis.


Requirements
------------
The following software is required to build the application:
-Java SDK 1.5
-Ant
-RBNB 2.5

The following software is required to run the application:
same as above

SET UP
- install rbnb
- install ant
- set the following environment variables:
RBNB_HOME   - the root of the rbnb installation

BUILDING
- RDV with event marker augmentation:
cd ${RDV_SRC}/branches/markers && ant clean jar

RUNNING
do an 'ant clean jar runMarkers'

